Prague transport companies are also promoting on a chip for the first time on Wednesday
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will enter the history of Prague’s transport companies as a date when the first passengers to embark on a subway, tram or bus will carry an electronic coupon in their pocket instead of a paper ticket.
These can currently buy about one hundred thousand people who own the chip card Opencard.
Passengers can purchase a 30-day, 90-day or annual coupon (valid from 1 January 2009) and have it played on their chip card at the same time, in the information centers and branches of the transport companies at the subway stations Muzeum, M<0xC5><0xAF>stek, Nádra<0xC5><0xBE>í Hole<0xC5><0xA1>ovice, Kolany<0xC5><0x9B>l, And<0xC4><0x9B>lis, Rozly<0xC5><0xA1>k.
The coupons have also been available on the Internet on the pages of the transport companies www.dpp.cz since yesterday.
The service was used by more than four hundred customers up to the afternoon hours.
Those who use internet sales can really forget about the output window in the subway stations, where they have had to wait regularly in long queues for their paper tickets.
You buy the coupon via the Internet, it is played on the Opencard in one of the thirteen branches of the city library.
