The authority orders that the driver, who had three official penalties for the alcohol level, installs this system in his car, which prohibits him from starting the car in the drunk state. If he is alcoholic, then the car does not start.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is already part of the report of the Attorney General. According to her, it is a pilot project that will last for a year.
The purpose is the rehabilitation of the driver, which is why he gets a course for retraining the traffic behavior.
In addition to the Public Prosecutor General, experience has shown that the Ministry of Transport and the Foundation of the Technical Institute for the Safety of Automobiles will also participate.
According to statistics, between 30-75% of drivers who were reported more than once for driving under the influence of alcohol returned to driving.
The ‘alcolock’ would prevent this because it is a system connected to the car, it measures the alcohol content in the exhaled air and prevents autostart when the driver has done an alcohol test; or if an alcohol concentration is found to be higher than allowed.
It costs more than 1 000 euros, the costs are borne by the person imposing the sanction.
In this context, a study conducted in the U.S. in 2007 showed that cars equipped with these devices prevent up to 65% of violations in the first year after their introduction.
In Spain, it is estimated that 115 lives could be saved each year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to tackle this behavior before it becomes a criminal offence.
And to facilitate their implementation, a lawful reform can be implemented in the usual way, and yet a reform of the Basic Law, which is necessary for the law enforcement process, is called for.
Still, the device is not available on the Spanish markets, in any store, although it has already been installed in some commercial vehicles and public transport vehicles.
Just tomorrow, the House of Representatives will vote on the initiative of the Spanish Socialist Workers’ Party, which proposes to install this system in school buses, which has already been done in France.
