Speaking in sleep
Some children talk at night
I do not mean those who wake up and tell us something that happened the day before, but the children who speak during sleep.
When it happens to you for the first time, at best you will be scared, but in reality it doesn’t matter.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and adolescents.
Certainly, more than one of you was told that you talked at night.
This phenomenon can occur occasionally (once in life, for example, during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month ), the next day the child can remember nothing.
There is no single reason that causes this phenomenon.
Often, relationships with other phenomena in sleep are sought, such as nightmares, panic anxiety at night, enuresis nocturna (wetting the bed at night), talking in sleep, but there is no reason for this.
As we mentioned earlier, it can be due to very high fiber, stress situations or overload.
In any case, this is a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It can be quiet speaking in single words, whispering or it can be quite the opposite (crying, crying, long discussions).
In cases where the utterance is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and seek advice from a specialist to check whether there is a problem that causes anxiety and thus arises.
We’ve said it’s a positive disorder, so it’s not treated, be it, it’s associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep apnea or with stress).
What you can do is perform a series of simple preventive measures:
Try not to arouse the child before sleeping.
So, choose calm play for the child and avoid stressful television programs that are awful and a little too wild.
In the nervous children who are recommended relaxation, relaxation methods can be used to help them get some inner peace.
This will help the child to sleep quietly.
When speaking occurs in sleep, try to keep calm.
Remember that it is harmless to the child and the next day it will not be able to remember anything that happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake it up.
This is useless, because the child is unconscious, so you will rip it out of sleep.
Although the child speaks, it sleeps, so it rests.
Remember, if after a couple of appearances it seems frightened, it is recommended to get advice or find out what the child is afraid of.
If they understand what it says (which is not so common), the child will not put pressure to conduct an interrogation and get more information out.
So you will not be able to achieve anything with it, because when the child is asleep, he is unconscious and cannot think about it.
Besides, you will hear what it says, but you will not know what it is dreaming and why it is saying, so be careful with the interpretation of the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
Perhaps, it doesn’t tell the child that you hear it at night and know its secrets.
Not even as a joke.
This causes a lot of fear.
So, don’t worry, it’s nothing bad, it’s a moment that only lasts a few minutes.
