The researchers hoped that the sight of the Virgin Mary among the faithful would evoke some sort of religious trance while selecting da Vinci’s image, because it was hardly different from the other painting and was felt to be reassuring.
The subjects each spent half an hour in an MRI scanner, and during that time received a total of 20 electroshocks in four stages, while either watching the religious, or the other painting.
The Catholics reported that they felt “safe” at the sight of the Mother of God, as if they were “cared for,” and they felt “calm and peace.”
